Kubernetes Handy commands
 - To deploy K8s charts in the name space "integration"
     make deploy_all KUBE_NAMESPACE=integration
 - To delete K8s charts in the name space "integration"
     make delete_all KUBE_NAMESPACE=integration
 - Monitor namespace "integration"
     watch kubectl get all,pv,pvc,ingress -n integration
 - Get logs of a container
     kubectl logs -n <<namespace>> <<podname>> <<container-name>>
     eg: kubectl logs -n integration tmcprototype-tmc-proto-test centralnode
 - Get the status of a pod - Which container are failing or passing
     kubectl describe pod <<podname>> -n <<namespace>>
     eg: kubectl describe pod tmcprototype-tmc-proto-test -n integration
 - Verify if the pods on the local system are running. All must be running for successful deployment
     kubectl get pods -n kube-system
 - Enter into a kubernetes pod
     kubectl exec -it pod/tmcprototype-tmc-proto-test -n integration -- /bin/bash

SKAMPI Deployment: For Low deployment DEPLOYMENT_CONFIGURATION=skalow
sudo make install DEPLOYMENT_CONFIGURATION=skamid
sudo make uninstall DEPLOYMENT_CONFIGURATION=skamid
make k8s_test MARK=skamid
With local archiver db connection details:
sudo make install DEPLOYMENT_CONFIGURATION=skalow ARCHIVER_HOST_NAME=xxx.xxx.xx.xx ARCHIVER_PORT=xxxx ARCHIVER_DB_USER=xxxx ARCHIVER_DB_PWD=xxxx ARCHIVER_DBNAME=test_db

For accessing Kibana in STFC environment, use URL:
https://k8s.stfc.skao.int/kibana/app/home#/

Webjive URLs:
Engageska cluster
http://192.168.93.80/tmcmid/taranta/devices
http://192.168.93.36/integration/taranta/devices
For accessing Webjive in STFC environment, use URL: 
https://k8s.stfc.skao.int/<<namespace>>/taranta/devices

Webjive dashboard restore and dump commands:
kubectl exec -i pod/mongodb-webjive-test-0 -n <namespace> -- mongorestore --archive < dashboard.dump
kubectl exec -i pod/mongodb-webjive-test-0 -n <namespace> -- mongodump --archive > dashboard.dump


